FunctionBody.FormulaText:
// Determines if supplied strings match based on the supplied boolean "CaseInsensitive" parameter. If the strings match, returns true, else false.
return Util.String.Compare(compareText1, compareText2, caseInsensitive) == 0;

// Returns the rule set name for the currently executing rule set.
return Context.RuleSet.Name;

// Returns true if the supplied rule is a language rule type.
return ruleElementType == "InRule.Repository.RuleElements.LanguageRuleDef";

// Returns true if the supplied rule element is a rule set type.
return ruleElementType == "InRule.Repository.RuleElements.RuleSetDef";

// Executes the supplied Explicit Entity Rule Set.
Context.Entity.ExecuteRuleSet(ruleSetName);

// Executes the supplied Explicit Entity Rule Set with parameters.
Context.Entity.ExecuteRuleSet(ruleSetName,param1Value,param2Value);

// Executes the supplied Independent Rule Set.
Context.CreateIndependentRuleSet(ruleSetName).Execute();

// Executes the supplied Independent Rule Set with parameters.
Context.CreateIndependentRuleSet(ruleSetName).Execute(param1Value,param2Value);

// Activates the supplied Rule Set
Context.Entity.ActivateRuleSet(ruleSetName);

// Returns true if the field is valid, and false if invalid.
return Context.Entity.Fields[fieldName].IsValid;

// Sets the value of the supplied field with the supplied value.
Context.Entity.Fields[fieldName].Value = value;

// Returns the value of the supplied field.
return Context.Entity.Fields[fieldName].Value;

// Returns the count of fields on the current entity.
return Context.Entity.Fields.Count;

// Returns the entity display name for the supplied entity.
return Context.GetEntity(entityId).GetDef().DisplayName;

// Returns the value of the supplied attribute key on the supplied field.
return Context.Entity.Fields[field].GetDef().Attributes[key].ToString();

// Returns true if the supplied date falls within Daylight Savings Time.
return checkDate.IsDaylightSavingTime();
